title: Amber Rose, Blac Chyna show cancelled after Kim Kardashian call - report
text:
Amber Rose, Blac Chyna show cancelled after Kim Kardashian call - report Amber Rose and Blac Chyna have reportedly pulled the plug on their new MTV reality show. Amber Rose, Blac Chyna show cancelled after Kim Kardashian call - report Models Blac Chyna (L) and Amber Rose attend the 2015 MTV Video Music Awards at Microsoft Theater on August 30, 2015 in Los Angeles, California. (Larry Busacca / Getty Images) Travel Deals Layla A. Jones Posted: Tuesday, October 13, 2015, 10:40 AM 
Amber Rose and Blac Chyna have reportedly pulled the plug on their new MTV reality show. 
Best friends Rose, 31, and Blac Chyna, 27, were nailing down the final contracts for the upcoming show in late August. However, the website is now reporting the show has been cancelled, though the reason why is unclear. 
Blac Chyna and Rose have apparently told friends that they’re each too busy with other business obligations. Rose is working on developing her own talk show and Blac Chyna working on her own product deals, TMZ said. 
The publication alleges, though, that the real reason the show won’t be happening is because Blac Chyna and Rose are no longer friends. The reason for the end to the publicity-filled friendship? Blac Chyna didn’t attend Rose’s L.A. slut walk last weekend and instead opted to party with rapper Future in Atlanta. Who's coming to hangout @PoolAfterDark in Atlantic City with me and my girl @Blacchyna & #Beatclan on 11/14?? #Skamlife �� A photo posted by Amber Rose (@amberrose) on Oct 9, 2015 at 3:24pm PDT 
Despite reports of a fractured friendship, both Rose and Blac Chyna still have photos of themselves together on Instagram, and will be hosting a party at Atlantic City’s Harrah’s on Nov. 14. 
RadarOnline has said that the pair's friendship is not at stake, but the Kardashian reputation was. Kim Kardashian apparently called Rose after her slut wak and expressed a desire to keep things amicable. "'Without being able to trash the Kardashians, they just felt like their show does not have much weight anymore,'" said an anoymous Radar source.
